    "description": {
        "en-US": "Thunderbird 3.0 and higher may display a new \"reply list\" button instead of \"reply all\", when the message appears to be part of a mailing list thread.  \"reply list\" deletes all other To: and Cc: recipients, and it is the default action whenever it is present.\n\nThere are at least two situations in which this behavior is undesirable:\n\n1) When one or more thread participants in the To: or Cc: lists are not actually subscribed to the mailing list themselves.  This is common when dealing with high-volume lists.\n\n2) When thread participants have configured their mail readers to flag messages in which the user appears in the To: or Cc: lists (indicating that those posts deserve more attention than the general \"background noise\" on the list).  For instance, Gmail displays an \"&gt;\" or \"&gt;&gt;\" icon next to threads in which the user has received replies, and displays nothing otherwise.\n\nThis add-on simply overrides the check for IsReplyListEnabled(), unconditionally returning false.  Thunderbird will then fall back to displaying the \"reply all\" button, as it did in previous releases."
    },
